1 Level 0

Level 0 refers to the un-clustered data, that is all of the data lives in one cluster.

1.1 Heat maps (Lv 0):

## Formatting data for heatmap by taking the column means.
## heatmap.2 requires at least two rows and columns. 
aggp <- apply(dat, 2, mean)
aggp <- t(cbind(aggp, aggp))

The following is a heatmap showing the averages of the marker values over the entire dataset. The reader should notice that the markers believed to be excitatory have higher means than do markersthe difference between groups of markers as compared with their believed classes.

heatmap.2(as.matrix(aggp),dendrogram='none',Colv=NA,trace="none", 
          col=mycol,colCol = ccol,labRow = "",cexRow=0.8, keysize=1.25,
          symkey=FALSE, symbreaks=FALSE,scale="none", srtCol=90)

1.2 Correlations: Lv 0

cmatfs <- cor(dat)
corrplot(cmatfs,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=1)

1.3 Heat maps (Lv 1):

## Formatting data for heatmap
aggp <- aggregate(dat,by=list(lab=L[[1]]),FUN=mean)
aggp <- as.matrix(aggp[,-1])
rownames(aggp) <- clusterFraction(L[[1]])
heatmap.2(as.matrix(aggp),dendrogram='row',Colv=NA,
          trace="none", col=mycol,colCol = ccol,cexRow=0.8, 
          keysize=1.25, symkey=FALSE,symbreaks=FALSE,
          scale="none", srtCol=90,
          )

1.4 Within cluster correlations (Lv 1)

corkp1 <- cor(dat[L[[1]] == 1,])
corkp2 <- cor(dat[L[[1]] == 2,])
difCor12 <- (corkp1 - corkp2)

layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,3), 2, 2, byrow=TRUE))
corrplot(corkp1,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 1")
corrplot(corkp2,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 2")
corrplot(difCor12,is.corr=FALSE,method="color",
         tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3","white","darkorange"))(50))
title("Difference(1,2)")

1.5 Heat maps (Lv 2):

## Formatting data for heatmap
aggp2 <- aggregate(dat,by=list(lab=L[[2]]),FUN=function(x){mean(x)}) 
aggp2 <- as.matrix(aggp2[,-1])
rownames(aggp2) <- clusterFraction(L[[2]])
heatmap.2(as.matrix(aggp2),dendrogram='row',Colv=NA,trace="none",
          col=mycol,colCol=ccol,cexRow=0.8, keysize=1.25,
          symkey=FALSE,symbreaks=FALSE,scale="none", srtCol=90)

Percentage of data within cluster is presented on the right side of the heatmap.

2 Within cluster correlations (Lv 2)

corLV2 <- lapply(c(1:4),function(x){cor(dat[L[[2]] == x,])})

difCor1112 <- ((corLV2[[1]] - corLV2[[2]]))
difCor2122 <- ((corLV2[[3]] - corLV2[[4]]))

layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,3,4,5,6,6), 4, 2, byrow=TRUE))
corrplot(corLV2[[1]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 1")
corrplot(corLV2[[2]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 2")
corrplot(difCor1112, method="color", tl.col=ccol, 
         tl.cex=0.8,
         mar = c(0,0,3,0),
         cl.lim = c(min(difCor1112,difCor2122),max(difCor1112,difCor2122)),
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3", 
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(100))
title("Difference(1,2)")
corrplot(corLV2[[3]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 3")
corrplot(corLV2[[4]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title("Cluster 4")
corrplot(difCor2122, method="color", tl.col=ccol, 
         tl.cex=0.8,
         mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         cl.lim = c(min(difCor1112,difCor2122),max(difCor1112,difCor2122)),
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3", 
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(100))
title("Difference(3,4)")

2.1 Heat maps (Lv 3):

## Formatting data for heatmap
aggp3 <- aggregate(dat,by=list(lab=L[[3]]),FUN=function(x){mean(x)})
aggp3 <- as.matrix(aggp3[,-1])
rownames(aggp3) <- clusterFraction(L[[3]])

The following are heatmaps generated from clustering via K-means++

heatmap.2(as.matrix(aggp3),dendrogram='row',Colv=NA,trace="none",
          col=mycol,colCol=ccol,cexRow=0.8, keysize=1.25,symkey=FALSE,
          symbreaks=FALSE,scale="none", srtCol=90)

2.2 Within cluster correlations (Lv 3)

corLV3 <- lapply(c(1:8),function(x){cor(dat[L[[3]] == x,])})

difCor1 <- (corLV3[[1]] - corLV3[[2]])
difCor2 <- (corLV3[[3]] - corLV3[[4]])
difCor3 <- (corLV3[[5]] - corLV3[[6]])
difCor4 <- (corLV3[[7]] - corLV3[[8]])
M <- max(difCor1, difCor2, difCor3, difCor4)
m <- min(difCor1, difCor2, difCor3, difCor4)

layout(matrix(c(1, 2, 3, 3,
                4, 5, 6, 6, 
                7, 8, 9, 9,
                10, 11, 12, 12), 8,2, byrow=TRUE))

corrplot(corLV3[[1]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8,
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 1')
corrplot(corLV3[[2]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8,
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 2')
corrplot(difCor1,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8,
         cl.lim=c(m,M), mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         is.corr= FALSE,
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3",
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(50))
title('Difference(1,2)')
corrplot(corLV3[[3]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 3')
corrplot(corLV3[[4]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 4')
corrplot(difCor2,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         cl.lim= c(m,M), mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         is.corr = FALSE,
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3",
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(50))
title('Difference(3,4)')
corrplot(corLV3[[5]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 5')
corrplot(corLV3[[6]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 6')
corrplot(difCor3,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8,
         cl.lim= c(m,M), mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         is.corr = FALSE,
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3",
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(50))
title('Difference(5,6)')
corrplot(corLV3[[7]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 7')
corrplot(corLV3[[8]],method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8, 
         mar=c(0,0,3,0))
title('Cluster 8')
corrplot(difCor4,method="color",tl.col=ccol, tl.cex=0.8,
         cl.lim= c(m,M), mar=c(0,0,3,0),
         is.corr = FALSE,
         col=colorRampPalette(c("#998ec3",
                                "white",
                                "darkorange"))(50))
title('Difference(7,8)')
